&quot;The Distant Future...&quot;
&quot;Vampires rule the night, but their numbers are dwindling.&quot;
&quot;With huge bounties on their heads, a class of hunters has emerged. Bounty Hunters.&quot;
&quot;One Hunter is unlike all the others. He is a Dunpeal-a half human, half vampire.&quot;
&quot;At war with himself, feared by all, tortured and alone, he is...&quot;

Vampire Hunter D!

Plot Summary: Continuing his quest to rid the world of the Nobility, the Vampire Hunter D, a dunpeal (half human, half vampire), is summoned by the Elbourne family to rescue their daughter Charlotte from the captivity of Meier Link. The race against time not only involves saving the girl, but also the additional hiring of the Markus Brothers; a volatile and infamous group of Hunters known for their tendency to rid themselves of the competition by any means neccessary. To make matters more complicated, when Charlotte is found she is more than reluctant to leave the side of her new love...

Review: http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/vampire-hunter-d-bloodlust 

I wasn't happy with how the 700mb copy looked on my PS3 + 32&quot; LCD so I encoded it myself. File is english only and has no subs, just like my Urban Vision DVD. Oddly(for an anime) the english language track was the master and it was dubbed in japanese. It shows.
